// Aliased import alias resolves in a type-declaration RECORD-FIELD member
// position (the canonical #2202 repro).
//
// `hew::aliassrc` exports a record `Payload`. The importer opts it in under the
// alias `Tag` (`import hew::aliassrc::{ Payload as Tag }`) and uses the alias as
// a `type` field's declared type: `type Boxed { item: Tag }`.
//
// The checker resolves type-decl member types in Pass 1 (`collect_types`),
// BEFORE imports are processed in Pass 2, so the bare alias `Tag` used to freeze
// as an unresolved `Named("Tag")` while its construction (Pass 3) resolved to
// the canonical `aliassrc.Payload` -- yielding a spurious
// `type mismatch: expected \`Tag\`, found \`aliassrc.Payload\``. The
// member-type re-resolution pass (run after imports are processed) upgrades the
// frozen member to the source identity, and HIR member-lowering stamps the same
// identity so the field read lowers end-to-end.
//
// Harness verb: hew run
// Expected: the code stored through the aliased-type field is read back.
import hew::aliassrc::{ Payload as Tag };

type Boxed {
    item: Tag;
}

fn main() {
    let b = Boxed { item: Tag { code: 50 } };
    println(b.item.code);
}
